commentTextItems.html: shorter ball pulled away through the infield and runs all the way to the boundary. Win for the Scots

commentPostTextItems.html: And that's it folks! This ODI series between Canada and Scotland has been drawn 1-1 after Scotland defeat Canada by 5 wickets.

Scotland were solid with the bat and chased down the Canadian total of 250 with solid half-centuries from Hamilton and Watson with McCallum finishing the job on 79*. After the cruel run-out for Watts at the start the Scots batted sensibly throughout and
were always on top of the run-rate. The Canadians are now flying to Holland tomorrow for two ODI's and a 4-day match while the Scots wait until August to host Ireland.
Thanks very much for joining me today and I hope you enjoyed our coverage. For now from Aberdeen it's goodbye from cricinfo and me Callum Stewart.

milestones.description: Dhaniram and Keshvani's 80-run partnership is CAN's highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 58 between Chumney and Codrington

stories.title: Scotland level series with five-wicket win
stories.subTitle: Scotland v Canada, 2nd ODI, Aberdeen
stories.summary: Chasing a target of 250, Gavin Hamilton, Ryan Watson and Neil McCallum guided the chase superbly to secure victory in the 48th over and level the series 1-1
